Text.SourceString: My dreams? I don’t even know where to begin. I have lots of dreams.//<portrait=normal>For instance, I would love to open my own bakery someday once I master pies and cakes.
Text.LocalizedString: My dreams? I don’t even know where to begin. I have lots of dreams.//<portrait=normal>For instance, I would love to open my own bakery someday once I master pies and cakes.

Text.SourceString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.

Text.SourceString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's just hope the government won’t close the school the first chance they get.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks, but that’s no perfume.//<portrait=normal>I think the scent that you smelled was from the cookies that I baked.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks, but that’s no perfume.//<portrait=normal>I think the scent that you smelled was from the cookies that I baked.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I don’t mind at all! I love baking.//<portrait=normal>Besides, I get to keep some of them for myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I don’t mind at all! I love baking.//<portrait=normal>Besides, I get to keep some of them for myself.

Text.SourceString: How are you doing today?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you doing today?

Text.SourceString: Yes, I work regular hours today.//No big deal, though, I like baking.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, I work regular hours today.//No big deal, though, I like baking.

Text.SourceString: Also, I get to come out of the kitchen smelling like cookies.//<portrait=normal>Who doesn’t love that?!
Text.LocalizedString: Also, I get to come out of the kitchen smelling like cookies.//<portrait=normal>Who doesn’t love that?!

Text.SourceString: Hello, neighbor!//Another Wednesday, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: Hello, neighbor!//Another Wednesday, eh?

Text.SourceString: The food here is so yum.//Lodeh, popiah, fried rice... I have to teach myself to make them, one of these days.
Text.LocalizedString: The food here is so yum.//Lodeh, popiah, fried rice... I have to teach myself to make them, one of these days.

Text.SourceString: *sigh*
Text.LocalizedString: *sigh*

Text.SourceString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me?//<portrait=annoyed>Oh no. Wednesday is my day off.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww... You were at Sam's looking for me?//<portrait=annoyed>Oh no. Wednesday is my day off.

Text.SourceString: Umm… No baking for me today.//<portrait=normal>I would rather spend my day off around the park or knit something pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… No baking for me today.//<portrait=normal>I would rather spend my day off around the park or knit something pretty.

Text.SourceString: I love the lake in the winter when everything is rigid and frozen...//It looks so clean and pretty.//Mesmerizing to look at.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the lake in the winter when everything is rigid and frozen...//It looks so clean and pretty.//Mesmerizing to look at.

Text.SourceString: Sunday is special for me.//<portrait=happy>I hang out at the tavern with Betty after work. Girls night in...//Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.
Text.LocalizedString: Sunday is special for me.//<portrait=happy>I hang out at the tavern with Betty after work. Girls night in...//Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.

Text.SourceString: I love how Betty and I can just talk and talk about baking...//And red velvet.//It turns out that we have a lot in common.
Text.LocalizedString: I love how Betty and I can just talk and talk about baking...//And red velvet.//It turns out that we have a lot in common.

Text.SourceString: You found me!//<portrait=normal>What's up?
Text.LocalizedString: You found me!//<portrait=normal>What's up?

Text.SourceString: I opened my window this morning, and the mist woke me up instantly.
Text.LocalizedString: I opened my window this morning, and the mist woke me up instantly.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I just love your style!//<portrait=normal>I like to pay attention to people's outfits around here. You know, for inspiration.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I just love your style!//<portrait=normal>I like to pay attention to people's outfits around here. You know, for inspiration.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith.//<portrait=concerned>You moved to an island and changed a career path.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith.//<portrait=concerned>You moved to an island and changed a career path.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I can ever do that…//<portrait=sad>Not courageous enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I can ever do that…//<portrait=sad>Not courageous enough.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that.//I hope I didn't bum you out.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that.//I hope I didn't bum you out.

Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad Randy is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four pupils.

Text.SourceString: Ah, you too, huh?//The food here makes me miss my parents too.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, you too, huh?//The food here makes me miss my parents too.

Text.SourceString: *sigh*
Text.LocalizedString: *sigh*

Text.SourceString: It really was. So yum!//I don't know what I would do if Frank stopped making red velvet cakes.
Text.LocalizedString: It really was. So yum!//I don't know what I would do if Frank stopped making red velvet cakes.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I did.//<portrait=sad>I tried copying Frank’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine isn't as good...
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I did.//<portrait=sad>I tried copying Frank’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine isn't as good...

Text.SourceString: For some reason, I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays.//<portrait=normal>You know, maybe it's a celebratory thing. Maybe...//<portrait=annoyed>In my mind, red velvet cakes equate to the end of a week.//I don't know.
